We were excited to have fish tacos so I found this place and decided to give it a try seeing the reviews it had acquired. I came here around 9:30pm on a Tuesday. They had no line and only two people eating there. When I ordered there was only one employee, he was really nice. He gave me to try a taro tortilla, which I found really tasty. I ordered two shrimp tacos with such tortilla and two fish tacos with regular corn tortillas.  The tacos were really big and I was full with only two of them. I didn't really know how they made it there, so I asked him to put a little of everything.  Here is what I found out from my visit.  Pros: Large sizes, enough to fill you up. Good value Really friendly staff Great location  Cons: A bit of a slow service Pico de gallo tasted a bit off. I think the tomatoes weren't fresh. When I ordered a little of everything as toppings I should have been warned the guacamole was an extra charge. I was charged around $1.75 for a table spoon worth of guacamole. Improper hygiene. Employee put on some gloves prior to handling food without previously handwashing. In the middle of food preparation he touched a tablet to change music, then failed to change gloves.  Were the tacos good? They weren't bad, I would say next time I go, I'll probably be selective with my toppings. I'll probably give this place a second change if I'm around the area. However, I wasn't impressed. They okay, nothing to love.
